
1. Why is accuracy important in ML model evaluation?

Accuracy measures correct prediction proportion in classification tasks: (TP + TN) / Total. It's the primary baseline metric for balanced datasets where classes occur with similar frequency.​

Engineering Con:


✅ Effective: Spam (50/50), Image classification (balanced)
❌ Misleading: Fraud detection (0.1% positive), Medical diagnosis (rare disease)

Decision Threshold: Use accuracy when positive/negative class balance > 80:20.



2. What is the difference between classification accuracy and regression error?

Fundamental Task Differences:

| Aspect     | Classification             | Regression                        |
| ---------- | -------------------------- | --------------------------------- |
| Output     | Discrete labels (cat, dog) | Continuous values (₹25.5L salary) |
| Metric     | Accuracy (0-1)             | Error (MSE, MAE, RMSE)            |
| Perfect    | 100% correct labels        | 0 error (exact predictions)       |
| Evaluation | Confusion matrix           | Residual plots                    |


Mathematical Distinction:


Classification: Accuracy = Σ(I[ŷᵢ = yᵢ]) / N
Regression:     MSE = (1/N) × Σ(yᵢ - ŷᵢ)²    # Lower is better



