4. Why is R² score useful in linear regression?

R² (Coefficient of Determination) quantifies variance explained by the model:


R² = 1 - (SS_res / SS_tot) = 1 - (Σ(yᵢ - ŷᵢ)² / Σ(yᵢ - ȳ)²)

Interpretation Ranges:

| R² Value  | Quality   | Salary Prediction Example    |
| --------- | --------- | ---------------------------- |
| 0.90-1.00 | Excellent | Explains 95% salary variance |
| 0.70-0.90 | Good      | Experience + education       |
| 0.50-0.70 | Fair      | Single feature (experience)  |
| 0.00-0.50 | Poor      | Random guessing              |

Critical Insight: R² = 0 → Model no better than mean predictor. R² < 0 → Model worse than baseline.

