5. How can visualization help understand model performance better?

Visuals reveal patterns that scalar metrics conceal:

python
# === 1. RESIDUALS PLOT (Regression diagnostics) ===
fig1 = make_subplots(rows=2, cols=2, 
                    subplot_titles=("Residuals", "Q-Q Plot", 
                                 "Pred vs Actual", "Confusion Matrix"))

# Residuals (heteroscedasticity detection)
residuals = y_true_reg - y_pred_reg
fig1.add_trace(go.Scatter(x=y_pred_reg, y=residuals, 
                         mode='markers', name='Residuals'), row=1, col=1)

# === 2. CONFUSION MATRIX (Classification errors) ===
cm = confusion_matrix(y_true_class, y_pred_class)
fig1.add_trace(go.Heatmap(z=cm, colorscale='Blues'), row=2, col=2)

st.plotly_chart(fig1, height=600)

Visualization ROI:


Scalar metrics: "85% accuracy" → Surface-level
Residual plots: "High variance at low predictions" → Actionable fix
Confusion matrix: "FN=15% in high-value segment" → Business priority


Diagnostic Patterns Detected:

| Visual Pattern   | Problem              | Solution            |
| ---------------- | -------------------- | ------------------- |
| Funnel residuals | Heteroscedasticity   | Log-transform Y     |
| Step function    | Non-linearity        | Polynomial features |
| Class imbalance  | Bias toward majority | SMOTE/undersampling |
| Outlier cluster  | Data quality         | Winsorize/remove    |


Production Evaluation Framework


CLASSIFICATION (Imbalanced): Precision/Recall/F1 > Accuracy
CLASSIFICATION (Balanced):  Accuracy + Confusion Matrix
REGRESSION:                 R² + RMSE + Residual plots

THRESHOLDS:
✅ Production: R² > 0.75, Accuracy > 0.85
⚠️  Review:    R² 0.60-0.75, Accuracy 0.75-0.85  
❌ Reject:     R² < 0.60, Accuracy < 0.75

